        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3158189924" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4953099692279831038">I was excited to read this book... I love the black and white look with the black edged pages. This was a very exciting book. Written from the perspective of the lawyer on the case, it’s filled with details of the investigation and suit. The book starts with a slow burn, getting to know the characters and setting but it’s well worth it in the end. This book has legal drama, mystery, suspense, and even a bit of family drama. I would have given five stars except that I’m not super into legal thril</span>
  <span id="freeText4953099692279831038" style="display:none">I was excited to read this book... I love the black and white look with the black edged pages. This was a very exciting book. Written from the perspective of the lawyer on the case, it’s filled with details of the investigation and suit. The book starts with a slow burn, getting to know the characters and setting but it’s well worth it in the end. This book has legal drama, mystery, suspense, and even a bit of family drama. I would have given five stars except that I’m not super into legal thrillers and it can be heavy on the details at times. You wouldn’t think that a book that starts with real estate law would be too interesting, but trust me... there’s much much more to it! I loved how the main character was portrayed and developed. Her flaws and past legal cases influenced her decision making throughout the process and we got a front row seat to that. I really loved her character. There were some funny and relatable moments too that really got me. I loved one of the beginning quotes when we are still getting to know her.... “having a bad hair day can distract a girl from any job”. Bottom line, if you like mysteries and “who dunnits” you’ll love this book... even more bonus points if you like legal thrillers! ⁣<br />⁣</span>
  <a data-text-id="4953099692279831038" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


